content:
Subscribe to Dashboards in Lightning Experience

Rather than manually refreshing a dashboard, you can subscribe to it. Subscribe yourself and other users, groups, or roles to receive refreshed dashboard results by email on a schedule that you set.

To subscribe to dashboards: Subscribe to Dashboards
To subscribe other people to dashboards: Subscribe to Dashboards: Add Recipients
To subscribe other people to dashboards by group or role: Subscribe to Dashboards: Send to Groups and Roles

Open the Lightning dashboard and click Subscribe, or on the Dashboards tab, select  | Subscribe.
In the Edit Subscription window, set the subscription schedule.
Add recipients or remove yourself.
Click Edit Recipients.
Select from the available entity types and start typing to see all the matching names.
Only the users, groups, or roles with permission to access the dashboard are listed.
Select from the matching options and click Add.
Close the Edit Recipients window.

If you want to refresh your dashboard on a schedule without emailing it to recipients, deselect Receive new results by email when dashboard is refreshed

Click Save.

The dashboard subscription starts, and recipients begin receiving dashboard results by email according to the schedule and conditions you set. For considerations, review Reports and Dashboards Limits and Allocations.
title: Subscribe to Salesforce Dashboards
